1 (h) An art therapist certified under KRS 309.130 engaged in providing mental
2 health services; or
3 (i) A pastoral counselor licensed under the provisions of KRS 335.600 to
4 335.699 engaged in providing mental health services; and
5 (8) "Mentally ill child" means that considering the child's age and development, the
6 child has a substantially impaired capacity to use self-control, judgment or
7 discretion in the conduct of the child's affairs and social relations, the child's
8 behavior is maladaptive or the child exhibits recognized emotional symptoms which
9 can be related to physiological, psychological or social factors.
10 Section 20. KRS 645.210 is amended to read as follows:
11 (1) After a notice of contest has been received, the hospital may continue the
12 hospitalization on an involuntary basis until a hearing has been held and the court
13 orders otherwise. In no case may the child be held more than fifteen (15) days
14 beyond the filing of the notice of contest, unless a certification hearing has been
15 held within seven (7) days of the filing of the notice of contest.
16 (2) A hearing to determine the necessity for continued hospitalization shall be held
17 within seven (7) days of the court's receipt of the notice of the contest. If the court
18 concludes that the child does not meet the criteria set out in KRS 645.090, the court
19 may order the child discharged or may enter an emergency custody order for
20 purposes of proceeding under other provisions of KRS Chapter 600 to 645 to secure
21 proper care for the child. The cabinet may place the child in a[ clinical] treatment
22 facility, mental health group home, or mental health care program.
23 Section 21. KRS 403.727 is amended to read as follows:
24 (1) Any petition filed under KRS 403.725 on behalf of a minor who is alleged to be a
25 victim of domestic violence and abuse, or in which a minor is named as a
26 respondent or petitioner, shall comply with the requirements in that section and
27 shall:
Page 52 of 55
SB012510.100 - 1631 - XXXX 3/2/2026 5:52 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 125/GA
1 (a) Proceed in accordance with the procedural safeguards under KRS 610.070;
2 and
3 (b) Conform to the confidentiality provisions under KRS 610.340.
4 (2) If the court orders an evidentiary hearing under KRS 403.730(1)(a), a guardian ad
5 litem shall be appointed for any unrepresented minor who is a respondent to the
6 action or a petitioner who is an alleged victim of domestic violence and abuse. The
7 guardian ad litem shall be paid a fee fixed by the court not to exceed five hundred
8 dollars ($500), which shall be paid by the Finance and Administration Cabinet.
9 (3) Violation of the terms or conditions of an order of protection issued under KRS
10 403.740 after the person has been served or given notice of the order shall
11 constitute contempt of court and may constitute a criminal offense pursuant to KRS
12 403.763 if the offender is an adult or a public offense under KRS 600.020[(51)] if
13 the offender is a juvenile. Once a juvenile action or contempt proceeding has been
14 initiated, the other shall not be undertaken regardless of the outcome of the original
15 proceeding.
16 (4) [Nothing in ]Subsection (3) of this section shall not preclude the Commonwealth
17 from proceeding, or the petitioner from pursuing charges, against the minor
18 respondent for offenses other than a violation of an order of protection. Proceedings
19 against a minor respondent for offenses other than a violation of an order of
20 protection shall proceed:
21 (a) In the juvenile session of District Court; and
22 (b) In accordance with the procedural and statutory provisions established for the
23 juvenile session of District Court.
