26 Section 23. The Justice and Public Safety Cabinet shall construct a high acuity
27 mental health facility to provide residential treatment for children in the custody of the
Page 54 of 55
SB012510.100 - 1631 - XXXX 3/2/2026 5:52 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 125/GA
1 Department of Juvenile Justice. The facility shall provide beds for a minimum of 24
2 children and shall be designed in a manner that shall allow for additions to the facility to
3 increase bed capacity as needed. The Justice and Public Safety Cabinet shall work with
4 the Cabinet for Health and Family Services to ensure compliance with all health facility
5 requirements, both federal and state. The provisions of this section, and the provisions of
6 subsection (1)(b)5. of Section 2 of this Act, are subject to funding in the executive branch
7 budget.
8 Section 24. The Cabinet for Health and Family Services shall provide or enter
9 into contracts or a memorandum of understanding with a public teaching university in
10 this state to provide clinical services to the high acuity health facility operated by the
11 Justice and Public Safety Cabinet through the Department of Juvenile Justice.
12 Section 25. The Justice and Public Safety Cabinet shall continue to implement
13 the plan to transition back to the regional model of juvenile detention facilities, and to
14 construct two female-only facilities as described in Section 2 of this Act, while
15 continuing to safely segregate males and females and violent and nonviolent offenders.
